newsArray.title: Why did Egypt win fewer medals at this year’s Olympics?
creator: Aisha Fareed
newsArray.description: article author: Mohamed El-ShamaaAuthor: Wed, 2024-08-14 13:01CAIRO: As the dust settles on the 2024 Paris Olympics, the Egyptian delegation walk away with just three medals.Ahmed Elgendy won gold in the modern pentathlon, Sara Samir claimed silver in weightlifting, and Mohamed Elsayed took bronze in fencing. Egypt’s most successful Olympics was in 2020, at the Tokyo Games. The team won six medals, including a gold for Feryal Ashraf in karate, a silver for Elgendy in the modern pentathlon, and bronze in taekwondo (Hedaya Malak and Saif Issa), wrestling (Mohamed Ibrahim Kisho) and karate (Giana Farouk.)Main category: SportTags: Paris Olympics#egyptEgyptian Ministry of Youth and SportsOsama Orabi
